  1. Differential expression analysis of in vivo data
    First, we read the raw read counts (three replicates per condition) and compare the samples (Table S1)
mice.data<-read.csv("input_files/mice_read_counts_24h.csv",row.names=1)
#Total reads per replicate
total.reads<-colSums(mice.data)
#DuffyNGS produces non-integer raw read count values, so we consider anything below one as zero.
non.zeroes<-sapply(1:ncol(mice.data),function(x){length(which(mice.data[,x]>=1))/nrow(mice.data)})*100
#Mean read counts among genes with non-zero counts
mean.count<-sapply(1:ncol(mice.data),function(x){mean(mice.data[mice.data[,x]>=1,x])})
#Standard deviation of read counts among genes with non-zero counts
sd.count<-sapply(1:ncol(mice.data),function(x){sd(mice.data[mice.data[,x]>=1,x])})
#Coefficient of variation
cv.count<-sd.count/mean.count
#Table S1
tableS1<-data.frame(round(non.zeroes,digits = 2),total.reads,round(mean.count,digits = 2),round(cv.count,digits = 2))
colnames(tableS1)<-c("Non-zero genes (%)","Total reads", "Mean count","CV")
print(tableS1[c(4:6,1:3),])

Second, we remove 3rd mice replicate (~85% zeroes) and genes with zero values in any of the remaining mice replicates

mice.count.tab <- mice.data
#Round read counts
mice.count.tab<-round(mice.count.tab)
#Delete 3rd mice replicate
mice.count.tab<-mice.count.tab[,-6]
#Only genes with non-zero values in both mice replicates are considered for differential expression analysis
deleted.genes<-which(mice.count.tab[,4]<1 | mice.count.tab[,5]<1)
mice.count.tab<-mice.count.tab[-1* deleted.genes,] 
print(paste("There are ",nrow(mice.count.tab)," remaining genes for downstream analyses",sep=""))

  1. Differential expression analysis of in vitro data
#Define files with raw read counts for in vitro data at 2h, 8h and 24h
runs<-c("2h","8h","24h")
files<-paste("input_files/read_counts_time",runs,".csv",sep="")
#list to save DESeq2 output
output.deseq.invitro<-list()
#list to save DEGs at each time point
invitro.deg<-list()
#list to save normalized counts
invitro.normalized.counts<-list()
#raw counts
invitro.raw.counts<-c()
# This loop runs DESeq2 for each time point 
for(q in 1:3)
{
invitro.counts <- read.csv(files[q],row.names = 1)
#save raw counts
if(q==1)
{
    invitro.raw.counts<-invitro.counts
}
else{
invitro.raw.counts<-cbind(invitro.raw.counts,invitro.counts)
}
#Round read counts
invitro.counts<-round(invitro.counts)
#Data frame with metadata
exp.metadata <- data.frame(condition = factor(rep(c("extracellular", "intracellular"), c(3,3))))
rownames(exp.metadata) <- colnames(invitro.counts)
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(invitro.counts, exp.metadata, ~condition)
#Save normalized counts
dds <- estimateSizeFactors(dds)
invitro.normalized.counts[[q]]<-assay(normTransform(dds))
#Remove genes with zero reads in all samples
dds <- dds[ rowSums(counts(dds)) > 1, ]
#Run main function
dds <- DESeq(dds)
#output
output.deseq <- results(dds)
#save output 
output.deseq.invitro[[q]]<-output.deseq
#save names of DEGs
invitro.deg[[q]]<-rownames(output.deseq)[which(output.deseq$padj < 0.01 & abs(output.deseq$log2FoldChange)>1)]
print(paste("# DEGs in the in vitro model at",runs[q],"is: ",length(invitro.deg[[q]])))
}

#Read  Rohde's expression matrix

#Convert gene names to upper case for comparing with DESeq2 output
rownames(rohde07)<-toupper(rownames(rohde07))

#Initial set of DEGs at 2h reported by Rohde et al. 2007
rohde.2h.up<-scan("rohde07.2h.txt",what="character")
Read 68 items
rohde.2h.up.in.pathSeq<-intersect(rohde.2h.up,rownames(invitro.raw.counts))
#Set of DEGs at 2h in both datasets
DEGs.2h.both.datasets<-intersect(rohde.2h.up,invitro.deg[["2h"]])
#Hypergeometric test 
#Number of successes 
q=length(DEGs.2h.both.datasets)
#Number of potential successes
m=length(rohde.2h.up.in.pathSeq)
#Others
n=length(transcripts.in.rohde07.and.pathSeq) - m
#Sample size
k=length(intersect(toupper(invitro.deg[["2h"]]),rownames(rohde07)))
p.value<-phyper(q-1,m,n,k,lower.tail=F)
tableS2<-rbind(tableS2,cbind(paste(length(rohde.2h.up), " (",m,")",sep=""),paste(length(invitro.deg[["2h"]]), " (",k,")",sep=""),q,p.value))

#We need to convert gene names to loci IDs
#Read locus-gene name table downloaded from MTB Portal 
mtb.geneNames<-read.table("mtb_portal_genes2111.txt",fill=T)
#Function to convert gene names to loci IDs 
convert.names<-function(namesToChange)
{
output<-c()
for(h in namesToChange)
{
 position.gene<-which(mtb.geneNames[,2]==h)
 if(length(position.gene)>0)
 {
   h=as.character(mtb.geneNames[position.gene,1])
 }
 output<-c(output,h)
}
output
}

  1. Generate input files for NetSurgeon
    NetSurgeon code can be downloaded in the Brent lab website (http://mblab.wustl.edu/software.html)
#Read ChIP-seq network binding in the -150bp,+70bp promoter region (from Minch et al 2015) plus operons
mtb.chip<-read.csv("final_chipseq_binding.csv",header=T)
#Load TF over-expression data (Rustad et al 2014) 
mtb.exp<-read.table("tfoe_data.txt",header=T,row.names = 1)
#Function that defines ChIP-seq network signs based on fold change threshold (fc.threshold)
fc_network_filter<-function(fc.threshold) 
{
  regulators<-unique(mtb.chip[,1])
  mtb.signedTRN<-matrix(nrow=nrow(mtb.exp),ncol=length(regulators),0,dimnames=list(rownames(mtb.exp),regulators))
  for(TF in regulators)
  {
      regulon<-as.vector(mtb.chip[which(mtb.chip[,1]==TF),2])
      if( TF %in% colnames(mtb.exp))
    {
      #Fold change vector
      current.oe<-(2^mtb.exp[,TF]) - 1 
      #Change to zero fold change absolute values below threshold
      positions.to.change<-which(abs(current.oe) < fc.threshold)
      mtb.exp[positions.to.change,TF]<-0
      #Assign signs based on fold change
      mtb.signedTRN[regulon,TF]<-sign(mtb.exp[regulon,TF])
      }
  }
  mtb.signedTRN
}
final.mtb.net<-fc_net_filter(0.2)
#Creating input for NetSurgeon original code (in vitro data)
for(q in 1:length(output.deseq.invitro))
{
 input.network = final.mtb.net
 input.dif.exp_analysis  = output.deseq.invitro[[q]]
 genes.present.in.both<-intersect(rownames(input_dif_exp_analysis),rownames(input_network))
 input.network<-input.network[genes.present.in.both,]
 #Only TFs with five or more targets are kept
 tfs.to.be.deleted<-which(colSums(abs(input.network))<5)
 input.network<-input.network[,-1*tfs.to.be.deleted]
 #NetSurgeon input network is TFs x Genes
 write.table(t(input.network),col.names=F,row.names=F,quote=F,file=paste("mtb_signed_network",
  runs[q],".mtr",sep=""))
q.values<-output.deseq.invitro[[q]][rownames(input.network),"padj"]
#Replace zeroes with minimum q-value among the non-zero ones (This is necessary to avoid infinity values)
zero.q.values<-which(q.values ==0)
if(length(zero.q.values)>0)
{
q.values[zero.q.values]<-min(q.values[-1* zero.q.values])
}
#Convert q-values of non-differentially expressed genes to 1
q.values[which(q.values > 0.01 | abs(output.deseq.invitro[[q]][rownames(input.network),"log2FoldChange"])< 1 )]=1
fc.sign<- sign(output.deseq.invitro[[q]][rownames(input.network), "log2FoldChange"])
#Sign -log q-values based on fold change direction
DEvector<- fc.sign * -log2(q.values) 
#Remove any NA
DEvector[which(is.na(DEvector))]<-0
write.table(DEvector,sep=" ",col.names=F,row.names=F,quote=F,file=paste("de",runs[q],".vect",sep=""))
regulators<-colnames(input.network)
write.table(regulators,sep=" ",col.names=F,row.names=F,quote=F,file=paste("mtb",runs[q],".tfs",sep=""))
targets<-rownames(input.network)
write.table(targets,sep=" ",col.names=F,row.names=F,quote=F,file=paste("mtb",runs[q],".orfs",sep=""))
}
#Creating input for NetSurgeon run (in vivo data)

#Sign -log q-values based on fold change direction
